{"author":{"id":"68dfa65ee618df2786e7da658bbfbbcc1f0c757170d9426e314e5f0886bcc55d"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1567244091,"nonce":"j5YoLo+MKZhouEUSRq1lXd+cF9A=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU0ODc3NTE2MjM=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2569","origin":"github"},"title":"hisat2 missing options","message":"While thinking about https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1740 I observed that some options are missing that could be handy, e.g. setting read groups (to fixed text or element identifier).\n\n```\n--no-unal | Suppress SAM records for reads that failed to align.\n--no-hd | Suppress SAM header lines (starting with @).\n--no-sq | Suppress @SQ SAM header lines.\n--rg-id \u003ctext\u003e | Set the read group ID to \u003ctext\u003e. This causes the SAM @RG header line to be printed, with \u003ctext\u003e as the value associated with the ID: tag. It also causes the RG:Z: extra field to be attached to each SAM output record, with value set to \u003ctext\u003e.\n--rg \u003ctext\u003e | Add \u003ctext\u003e (usually of the form TAG:VAL, e.g. SM:Pool1) as a field on the @RG header line. Note: in order for the @RG line to appear, --rg-id must also be specified. This is because the ID tag is required by the SAM Spec. Specify --rg multiple times to set multiple fields. See the SAM Spec for details about what fields are legal.\n--omit-sec-seq | When printing secondary alignments, HISAT by default will write out the SEQ and QUAL strings. Specifying this option causes HISAT to print an asterix in those fields instead.\n```","files":null}]}